<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<subsection xml:id="subsec-4-2-1-what-is-a-direct-proof" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>What is a Direct Proof?</title>
    
    

    <p>Now without further ado - the direct proof.</p>

    <assemblage>
        <title>Direct Proof of <m>P\implies Q</m></title>
      <idx><h>direct proof</h><h>steps</h></idx>
        <p>
          Assume <m>P</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\vdots</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Therefore <m>Q</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Thus <m>P\implies Q</m>
        </p>
      </assemblage>
    
      <p>
        Here is where the title of the text becomes clear:
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>{\color{red}{\text{Beginning}}}</m> -- Assume <m>P</m>
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>{\color{green}{\text{Muddle}}}</m> -- ...
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>{\color{blue}{\text{End}}}</m>  -- Therefore <m>Q</m>
      </p>

</subsection>